title: China's Tiangong-1 space module breaks up over South Pacific - Xinhua
text:
April 2, 2018 / 1:07 AM / Updated 8 minutes ago China's Tiangong-1 space module breaks up over South Pacific - Xinhua Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
BEIJING (Reuters) - China’s Tiangong-1 space module re-entered the earth’s atmosphere at 8:15 a.m. (0015GMT) on Monday over the South Pacific and mostly burnt up on re-entry, state news agency Xinhua said. FILE PHOTO: A model of the Tiangong-1 space lab module (L), the Shenzhou-9 manned spacecraft (R) and three Chinese astronauts is displayed during a news conference at Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center, in Gansu province, China June 15, 2012. REUTERS/Jason Lee/File Photo Reporting by Ben Blanchard, Cheng Fang and Lusha Zhang; Editing by Paul Tait
